# AXIS AI Agent — Cursor Rules
# Full details: see AXIS_PLAYBOOK.md

## Project Identity
- Project name: AXIS (Agentic X-interface Intelligent System)
- Language: Python 3.11.9
- OS Target: Windows

## Mandatory Rules

### 1. i18n — Zero Hardcoded Strings
- NEVER write raw text in print(), logging, or Telegram messages.
- ALWAYS use: `lang.get("key")` from `core.i18n`
- ALWAYS add new keys to: `config/locales/en.json`, `uk.json`, `es.json`

### 2. Guardian Protocol
- ANY destructive action (delete, git push, system change) MUST use `ask_user_confirmation()` from `telegram_bridge`.

### 3. Code Quality
- Type hints: REQUIRED on every function signature
- Docstrings: Google-style on every public class and method
- No bare `print()` in production — use `logging` to `logs/axis.log`
- Error handling: always catch exceptions and report via `lang.get()`

### 4. Architecture
- `core/` — orchestration only, no skill logic
- `agent_skills/` — one subfolder per skill, self-contained
- Skills must NOT import from each other directly
- Use `mcp_hub` for file/GitHub access when available

### 5. Windows Environment
- Use `encoding='utf-8'` when opening files
- Background threads must use `daemon=True`

## New Skill Checklist
1. Create folder under `agent_skills/`
2. Add `manifest.py` with functions + EXPORTED_TOOLS list
3. Use `lang.get()` for all output strings
4. Apply Guardian Protocol to destructive actions
5. Add locale keys to all 3 JSON files
